00:49.883 --> 00:53.803
Some people can see
all your mistakes.

00:53.929 --> 00:56.597
The way you hold it
in your shoulders.

00:56.724 --> 01:01.018
Show it in your face.

01:01.019 --> 01:03.813
I made a lot of mistakes
in my life

01:03.939 --> 01:08.025
and they were
my mistakes.

01:08.026 --> 01:10.695
Nobody else's.

01:10.821 --> 01:13.072
Mine.

01:13.198 --> 01:15.283
When you get older,
all those mistakes

01:15.409 --> 01:18.703
start piling up inside you.

01:18.829 --> 01:22.165
Regrets, blame.

01:24.042 --> 01:26.210
It's enough to make you
sick to your stomach.

01:29.131 --> 01:32.717
Problem is,
there are certain things

01:32.843 --> 01:34.927
that I just can't
change about myself.

01:55.449 --> 01:57.283
Fill it up, will you?

02:03.957 --> 02:06.626
- Morning.
- Good morning.

02:06.752 --> 02:08.085
$20 on eight, please?

02:12.299 --> 02:14.008
Where are your cards?

02:14.092 --> 02:17.428
Cards... Backside of
this aisle right here.

02:31.109 --> 02:33.236
He almost finished
out there?

02:33.362 --> 02:34.946
Yeah, almost.

02:43.413 --> 02:47.041
9-1-1. What's your emergency?

02:47.125 --> 02:50.378
Hello? What's the address
of your emergency?

02:54.132 --> 02:55.675
That'll be it.

02:55.801 --> 02:59.136
Okay, $20 on
the pump, $24.

02:59.221 --> 03:01.305
$24. That's a steal.

03:06.854 --> 03:08.521
You have a good day.

03:16.196 --> 03:17.738
Boy.

03:25.372 --> 03:27.164
You're the one
from the paper.

03:27.165 --> 03:30.918
I think you got me confused
with somebody else, all right?

03:31.044 --> 03:33.880
No. I know who you are.

03:34.006 --> 03:36.173
I know who he is too.

03:51.565 --> 03:55.192
The truth, sir...

05:00.092 --> 05:02.259
I assume you're a friend.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.594
I'm sorry.

05:03.720 --> 05:06.514
A friend of
the family?

05:06.640 --> 05:07.515
Yeah.

05:07.641 --> 05:09.100
I'm sorry for your loss.

05:11.979 --> 05:13.771
What's gonna happen
with the boy?

05:13.897 --> 05:16.440
He's going to his
grandparents' place.

05:16.566 --> 05:18.192
Where were they?

05:18.276 --> 05:21.070
They live in
Farmington, New Mexico.

05:21.196 --> 05:23.280
But I hear his
grandfather's gravely ill.

05:23.365 --> 05:25.366
You driving him?

05:25.492 --> 05:28.869
Oh, no. I'm just gonna chauffer him
over to the bus station.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.287
Do you know Louis?

05:30.288 --> 05:31.831
No.

05:31.957 --> 05:34.375
Thank the Lord,
he's got his grandparents.

05:34.501 --> 05:35.960
Yeah.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.589
All right, son.
You ready?

05:40.716 --> 05:42.383
Yes, sir.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.719
Let me help you.

05:48.932 --> 05:50.516
Right over here.

06:00.569 --> 06:02.570
All right, son.

06:10.912 --> 06:13.622
So all right.
Here we go.

06:13.749 --> 06:14.999
Now I've got your ticket.

06:15.125 --> 06:16.417
Your money's
in the envelope.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.669
They're gonna put your skis
and bags underneath.

06:20.839 --> 06:24.133
I hate buses.

06:24.259 --> 06:25.593
Can't you
just drive me?

06:25.719 --> 06:28.637
Aw, son, I'm needed here.
But you'll be fine.

06:28.764 --> 06:30.556
Nothing to worry about, okay?

06:32.517 --> 06:35.311
It's uh...
It was nice meeting you.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.104
You too, Louis.

06:39.524 --> 06:42.109
I'll be praying
for you, son.

07:28.907 --> 07:32.785
Hey, Louis.
I'm John.

07:32.911 --> 07:34.495
Yeah, you were at the church.

07:34.621 --> 07:36.330
That's right, that's right.

07:36.414 --> 07:37.665
Nice to meet you.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.291
Listen, I'm sorry
about your mother.

07:39.417 --> 07:40.459
It's a shame.

07:42.420 --> 07:45.422
Listen, I just got a phone call
from your grandparents.

07:45.423 --> 07:46.966
Apparently, they don't
love the idea of you

07:47.092 --> 07:49.927
riding on this bus
for three days.

07:50.053 --> 07:51.345
They asked me if
I'd give you a lift.

07:51.429 --> 07:52.763
Meanwhile, I was headed
that way

07:52.889 --> 07:54.431
so I told them, shit, why not?

07:56.434 --> 07:58.602
Sir, I don't know you.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.730
Yeah, well, I don't really
know you either and,

08:01.857 --> 08:03.440
frankly, this is
a pain in my ass.

08:03.441 --> 08:06.110
But, like I said,
I know your grandparents

08:06.236 --> 08:09.446
and your mother was a...
She was a good woman.

08:09.531 --> 08:12.741
You knew my mom?

08:12.868 --> 08:14.326
Yeah.

08:14.452 --> 08:15.772
She never really
talked about you.

08:15.871 --> 08:16.745
Yeah?

08:16.872 --> 08:21.709
Well, I guess I didn't make much of
an impression then, did I?

08:21.835 --> 08:23.586
We kept in touch.
I'd call, she'd call.

08:23.712 --> 08:25.504
- You know how it goes.
- Yeah.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.381
Listen, I got to hit the road.

08:27.465 --> 08:29.383
I understand if you don't
want to come with me.

08:29.467 --> 08:31.010
Besides, buses ain't so bad.

08:31.136 --> 08:35.472
Perfectly civilized mode of
transportation, if you ask me.

08:35.472 --> 08:38.017
But, hey,

08:38.143 --> 08:41.520
good luck to you, kid,

08:41.645 --> 08:47.026
and my deepest condolences to
you and your family, all right?

08:50.947 --> 08:53.324
Kid, you getting
on the bus? I gotta go.

08:57.412 --> 08:58.495
Sir.

08:58.496 --> 09:00.164
Sir?

09:10.133 --> 09:12.676
Get in.

09:17.807 --> 09:22.228
You, uh... You live in
this car or something?

09:22.354 --> 09:23.520
No, of course not.

09:23.521 --> 09:25.564
I just wasn't
expecting guests.

09:41.164 --> 09:43.082
Your mother was
a wonderful woman.

09:43.208 --> 09:47.920
Classy lady, fun gal.
Full of spirit.

09:48.046 --> 09:48.921
She was...

09:49.047 --> 09:53.425
Sparky.

09:55.011 --> 09:56.095
- Oh...
- She was...

09:56.221 --> 09:57.596
I forgot.

09:59.557 --> 10:03.435
What do you got there?
Pictures.

10:03.561 --> 10:04.561
Ah.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.563
This is
my grandparents' house.

10:06.564 --> 10:11.568
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Good, that's good.

10:15.573 --> 10:19.576
You know, the only time I really visited
them was when I was little.

10:19.661 --> 10:22.288
Mom didn't get along with
my grandparents too well.

10:22.414 --> 10:24.581
Didn't really talk.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.251
Hey, how long do you
think it'll take?

10:27.377 --> 10:28.919
I don't know.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.175
What?

10:36.886 --> 10:38.595
Nothing.

10:40.598 --> 10:42.516
Hey, I got to make
a couple quick calls.

10:42.600 --> 10:44.727
Should just take me
a couple minutes.

10:56.614 --> 10:59.325
- Moody residence.
- Mrs. Moody?

10:59.451 --> 11:02.202
John Wheeler here.
How you doing?

11:02.329 --> 11:05.122
You have got some
nerve calling here.

11:05.248 --> 11:08.625
I was just at your daughter's
wake. Where were you?

11:08.626 --> 11:12.296
Earl's sick.
Now what do you want?

11:14.090 --> 11:16.133
I got Louis, her boy.

11:16.259 --> 11:18.510
What... why would
you have Louis?

11:18.636 --> 11:20.596
Now, look, there's been
a change of plans.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.639
I'm gonna drive him home.

11:22.640 --> 11:25.434
Where's that priest?
Put Louis on the phone.

11:25.560 --> 11:26.727
It'll just take
a couple of days.

11:26.853 --> 11:28.520
You got nothing
to worry about.

11:28.646 --> 11:32.649
Now you put Louis back on
that bus and get back...

11:41.576 --> 11:43.410
One more stop.

12:14.401 --> 12:15.651
Stay here.

12:15.735 --> 12:17.694
Hey, I need that
to get home!

12:22.992 --> 12:25.661
What's up, John?

12:26.621 --> 12:30.290
Will you excuse us
for a moment, please?

12:30.417 --> 12:31.708
Okay, thanks.

12:50.728 --> 12:52.729
This is a fucking joke,
right?

12:52.730 --> 12:55.274
There's a little over
6,000 bucks right there.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.902
You're short $14,000
and change. Maybe more.

12:59.028 --> 13:01.780
Well, what are you...
you said $10,000.

13:01.906 --> 13:03.449
I owe you $10,000.

13:03.575 --> 13:08.245
You're late, John, again.
So it's $20.

13:08.371 --> 13:12.875
What are you doing, huh?

13:13.001 --> 13:14.668
How long have
we known each other?

13:14.752 --> 13:17.296
Long enough for you
to know better.

13:17.422 --> 13:19.840
This is fucking bullshit, John!
Do you understand?

13:19.966 --> 13:23.760
What the fuck
do you want from me?

13:23.845 --> 13:25.762
John,

13:25.763 --> 13:29.766
protection in jail
is very expensive.

13:29.767 --> 13:31.435
Do you understand that?

13:31.561 --> 13:33.770
I didn't ask you for
any goddamned protection.

13:33.771 --> 13:35.939
Yeah, but you took it.

13:36.065 --> 13:38.609
You know jail could have
been dangerous for you, John.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.405
I'm living out of my car.

13:45.783 --> 13:47.951
I don't have
anything else.

13:48.077 --> 13:49.797
I just gave you everything
that I got, okay?

13:49.871 --> 13:53.123
Boy, do you want
to go back to jail?

13:53.249 --> 13:55.459
You like the bed and the three meals of
crap they serve you every day?

13:55.585 --> 13:58.378
'Cause I can arrange that with
just one fucking phone call.

13:58.505 --> 13:59.671
Freddy, give me
the fucking phone.

13:59.797 --> 14:00.797
No, no, no, no.

14:00.882 --> 14:02.362
You're not gonna
make any phone calls.

14:02.425 --> 14:04.801
I got just as much shit
on you as you got on me.

14:04.886 --> 14:07.763
6,000 bucks.
That's all you get.

14:45.260 --> 14:47.261
We're closed!

14:48.680 --> 14:50.222
We're closed!

14:54.686 --> 14:56.478
Goddamn kid.

15:18.501 --> 15:20.627
Hey, are you in
some kind of trouble?

15:23.881 --> 15:28.594
It's nothing.

15:28.720 --> 15:31.263
Did they
do that to you?

15:31.389 --> 15:33.140
I don't know
what I was thinking.

15:33.266 --> 15:34.891
You ain't worth the trouble.

15:48.197 --> 15:52.451
The closest I could
get you is Albuquerque.

15:52.577 --> 15:56.788
I'll call your grandma and have her
pick you up in a couple of days.

15:56.914 --> 15:58.665
Good to meet you.

17:20.580 --> 17:22.958
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

17:23.041 --> 17:24.792
Louis!

17:27.088 --> 17:28.630
Louis!

17:35.930 --> 17:37.055
Louis?

17:40.184 --> 17:42.060
Louis.

17:47.275 --> 17:50.902
Hey.

17:51.028 --> 17:53.029
Hey, I'm talking to you.

17:59.954 --> 18:02.038
I don't want
to be alone.

18:08.504 --> 18:12.048
Why did she have to die?

18:14.302 --> 18:17.012
There's no good reason.

18:17.096 --> 18:20.056
I don't know, man.

18:21.058 --> 18:23.310
I don't have anyone else.

18:26.439 --> 18:29.399
Hey, you're
gonna be all right.

19:28.000 --> 19:31.753
Hey! Hey!

19:34.340 --> 19:37.384
Hey, let's get
something to eat.

19:37.510 --> 19:39.344
I'm hungry.

19:40.930 --> 19:42.931
What's with these skis?

19:43.057 --> 19:45.100
For skiing.

19:45.184 --> 19:48.103
Yeah, well, there ain't
no snow around here.

19:51.148 --> 19:52.858
The skis were a gift
from my mom.

19:52.984 --> 19:55.026
You probably never
even skied before.

19:55.152 --> 19:56.695
She wanted me to learn.

19:56.821 --> 19:58.154
Skiing's expensive.

19:58.239 --> 20:00.156
I just saved you
a shitload of money.

20:00.157 --> 20:01.867
It was the last thing
she gave me before she died.

20:01.993 --> 20:03.869
Yeah, it's a dumb sport.

20:03.995 --> 20:06.475
I can't believe all you got was
$20 bucks and that stupid ring!

20:06.581 --> 20:08.498
Are you hungry?
I'm starving.

20:08.624 --> 20:09.833
Let's go.

20:15.882 --> 20:18.758
Mm, mm.

20:18.885 --> 20:21.177
Good.

20:22.597 --> 20:25.891
What, you're not gonna eat?

20:26.017 --> 20:27.183
I'm not hungry.

20:27.268 --> 20:29.811
Fine with me. Starve.

20:33.983 --> 20:35.942
Look at that
little piece of ass.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.739
Hey, you like women?

20:40.865 --> 20:42.449
Yeah, I guess.

20:42.575 --> 20:44.659
You guess?

20:44.785 --> 20:47.120
All right, well, know this.

20:47.204 --> 20:48.872
A scorned woman will
tear your heart out,

20:48.998 --> 20:51.082
put it between
two buns and eat it

20:51.208 --> 20:53.668
just as your life
slips away before you.

20:53.794 --> 20:56.212
Don't ever forget that.

20:57.298 --> 20:59.174
Hey, you wanna drive?

21:01.427 --> 21:03.970
Yeah? You wanna drive?

21:05.222 --> 21:07.474
All right, can you
see over the hood?

21:07.600 --> 21:09.392
I guess.

21:09.518 --> 21:11.978
All right.
Your feet touch the pedals?

21:12.104 --> 21:13.813
I think so.

21:13.940 --> 21:16.608
You think so or you can?
It's kind of a big deal.

21:16.734 --> 21:18.193
- Yeah, fine.
- Okay, all right.

21:18.277 --> 21:19.945
So this is an automatic.

21:20.071 --> 21:22.781
So all you gotta do is pull that
lever down from P to D.

21:22.907 --> 21:24.240
There you go.

21:24.241 --> 21:26.409
All right, now take your
foot off the brake.

21:26.535 --> 21:29.579
Push down on the gas.

21:29.705 --> 21:31.414
There you go.

21:35.836 --> 21:38.922
All you gotta do is avoid other
cars and that's pretty much it.

21:39.966 --> 21:41.174
How fast you going?

21:41.258 --> 21:43.259
Uh, 32 mph.

21:43.260 --> 21:44.970
No, no, no.
You gotta get it up.

21:45.096 --> 21:47.263
At least 50 or 60, even 70.

21:49.892 --> 21:54.270
There you go. See, faster is
way better, isn't it?

21:56.357 --> 21:57.440
You're blind! Oh!

21:57.566 --> 21:59.526
Oh!

22:03.197 --> 22:07.325
All right, the first rule to
gun fighting is having a gun.

22:07.451 --> 22:09.744
All right, I prefer
to have something small.

22:09.870 --> 22:11.454
Something easier to carry.

22:11.580 --> 22:13.873
Easier to conceal,
all right?

22:14.000 --> 22:15.750
Can't go hunting with
something like this, though.

22:15.876 --> 22:17.085
Why not?

22:17.211 --> 22:19.754
You just can't.
It ain't right.

22:19.880 --> 22:21.297
What's the point, then?

22:21.382 --> 22:23.883
The point is,
if I have the gun...

22:25.302 --> 22:28.430
I have the control, right?

22:28.556 --> 22:30.849
You want to give it a shot?

22:34.103 --> 22:36.396
If I let you shoot this,
you owe me a favor.

22:36.522 --> 22:37.981
Okay.

22:38.107 --> 22:39.315
All right.

22:41.736 --> 22:43.319
Go ahead.

22:52.329 --> 22:55.498
Go ahead,
shoot it again.

22:58.794 --> 22:59.669
All right.

22:59.795 --> 23:02.839
Turn it, gangster style.

23:02.965 --> 23:04.466
There you go.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.094
Let's go.

23:12.433 --> 23:14.476
Hey, give me my gun.

23:34.371 --> 23:38.374
Wake up.
Wake up.

23:40.252 --> 23:41.795
It's time for that favor.

24:01.690 --> 24:04.692
All right, now keep
the engine running.

24:04.819 --> 24:07.403
Don't turn it off for any
reason, you understand?

24:07.404 --> 24:09.322
Where you going?

24:09.406 --> 24:12.075
I gotta run inside and
grab a couple of things.

24:12.201 --> 24:13.284
Just keep it running.
I'll be right back.

24:13.410 --> 24:15.411
Now jump in
the driver's seat.

24:15.412 --> 24:17.205
Wait, what?

24:30.594 --> 24:33.429
- Howdy.
- Howdy.

24:37.059 --> 24:40.436
Let me know if I can
help you with anything.

24:40.437 --> 24:44.023
We got some
specials back there.

25:23.772 --> 25:26.357
Are you gonna get it?

25:26.483 --> 25:30.153
Yeah, that should...
oh, the newspaper.

25:30.279 --> 25:31.487
Get on the ground.

25:36.994 --> 25:38.661
Get on the fucking ground!

25:40.497 --> 25:43.458
- Get on the goddamned...
- I heard you!

25:43.542 --> 25:45.982
- I'll beat you with this fucking gun!
- I heard you, damn it!

26:03.520 --> 26:07.315
Listen, this store's all I got.
You leave me something you hear?

26:07.441 --> 26:08.483
There you go.

26:08.567 --> 26:10.526
You're a real
son of a bitch.

26:14.990 --> 26:16.491
Hey! What the hell
are you doing?

26:16.575 --> 26:19.410
Hey, hey!

26:19.536 --> 26:21.454
Get out of the fucking car!
Get out...

26:21.538 --> 26:22.997
Hands off the boy!

26:23.123 --> 26:25.250
Easy, easy!

26:25.376 --> 26:26.960
Go!

26:31.590 --> 26:33.216
Ha!

26:33.342 --> 26:35.510
All right!
Now keep it up over 70.

26:35.594 --> 26:37.074
Keep it on the right side
of the road.

26:37.137 --> 26:38.471
- Just like I told you.
- I'm gonna be sick.

26:38.555 --> 26:40.265
What do you mean,
you feel sick?

26:40.391 --> 26:42.558
- I'm sick, I'm sick.
- What are you doing?

26:42.559 --> 26:43.559
Hey! Hey!

26:43.560 --> 26:45.895
Get in the back!
Get in the back!

26:46.021 --> 26:48.147
Go, go, go, go!

26:52.403 --> 26:55.697
Oh, shit!
God damn it!

26:59.493 --> 27:01.369
Son of a bitch!

27:01.495 --> 27:03.579
- I need some air.
- Yeah, well, shut up!

27:06.792 --> 27:08.376
I need air.

27:13.090 --> 27:14.549
- I need some air!
- What are you doing?

27:14.633 --> 27:16.759
Shut that door!

27:20.014 --> 27:21.556
No!

27:26.520 --> 27:28.104
No!

27:28.230 --> 27:32.025
God damn it! God damn it!

27:46.332 --> 27:48.958
Stay here.

27:49.084 --> 27:50.877
Where you going?

28:09.313 --> 28:11.439
Get your things.

28:11.565 --> 28:13.775
- Where'd you get that car?
- Shut up and get in!

28:13.901 --> 28:15.568
Did you steal it?

28:15.652 --> 28:19.489
I will leave you here.
I swear to God, I will!

28:39.343 --> 28:42.678
You cost me a lot
of money today.

28:42.679 --> 28:45.681
I don't want anything
to do with you.

28:45.682 --> 28:49.227
Well, that's not
an option, is it?

28:49.353 --> 28:52.438
You can't make me stay.

28:52.564 --> 28:53.606
I can leave.

28:53.690 --> 28:55.233
Just hitchhike.

28:55.359 --> 28:58.611
Yeah, okay.
You're gonna hitchhike?

28:58.695 --> 29:00.446
Yeah.

29:05.702 --> 29:09.997
Why don't we find a place
to sleep tonight?

29:10.124 --> 29:10.998
With a bed?

29:11.125 --> 29:14.001
Yeah, sure.
Why not?

29:14.128 --> 29:16.712
Fine.

29:27.141 --> 29:29.642
You awake?

29:29.726 --> 29:31.477
What?

29:31.603 --> 29:33.729
Just wanted to see
if you were awake.

29:39.528 --> 29:40.736
Why'd you do it?

29:40.737 --> 29:41.737
Do what?

29:41.738 --> 29:44.449
Rob that place.

29:44.575 --> 29:48.744
Because we didn't have
any money and we needed it.

29:48.745 --> 29:50.329
To get me home?

29:50.456 --> 29:52.415
Yeah, to get you home.

29:52.541 --> 29:54.625
Food and gas.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.128
This bed.

29:57.254 --> 29:59.088
Why do you live in your car?

30:01.758 --> 30:04.760
Because I can't
