♪ On that beautiful shore ♪

43:21.557 --> 43:23.642
- Praise the Lord!
- Praise the Lord!

43:23.768 --> 43:26.061
- Amen!
- Amen!

43:26.187 --> 43:30.565
I am so pleased to see some
visitors with us this morning.

43:31.818 --> 43:34.528
Come on up here, son.

43:34.612 --> 43:37.030
Come on up here, son!

43:37.156 --> 43:38.448
I'm not gonna bite you.

43:38.574 --> 43:39.825
Come join me here.

43:39.951 --> 43:42.619
There you go.
Let him by there.

43:42.745 --> 43:44.913
Here you are.

43:45.039 --> 43:46.581
What is your name, son?

43:46.582 --> 43:47.582
Louis.

43:49.043 --> 43:51.503
Everyone please welcome
our child of God, Louis.

43:51.587 --> 43:53.630
- Welcome, Louis.
- Welcome.

43:53.756 --> 43:55.382
What is your name?

43:55.508 --> 43:56.883
John.

43:57.010 --> 43:58.176
- John.
- Yep.

43:58.303 --> 43:59.344
Why won't you join us?

43:59.470 --> 44:01.096
Nah, I'm good right here.

44:01.222 --> 44:03.307
No, no. I'm extending my hand
in the name of the Lord

44:03.433 --> 44:05.600
so we may greet you
as a congregation.

44:05.601 --> 44:09.146
If you wouldn't mind removing your cap
here in the house of the Lord?

44:13.276 --> 44:16.403
Everyone please welcome
these brothers in Christ,

44:16.529 --> 44:18.697
John and Louis.

44:18.823 --> 44:20.907
Welcome, John and Louis.

44:21.034 --> 44:23.952
Thank you.

44:24.078 --> 44:25.537
Thank you.

44:25.621 --> 44:26.955
Yeah, can we sit?

44:27.081 --> 44:28.373
- Please do.
- All right.

44:28.499 --> 44:30.876
Take your seat, gentlemen.

44:45.683 --> 44:48.226
We don't see too many
new faces around here.

44:48.353 --> 44:50.645
It's exciting when we do.

44:50.646 --> 44:52.397
We won't be staying for long.

44:52.523 --> 44:54.191
What, you just
passing through?

44:54.317 --> 44:55.942
Yeah.

44:56.069 --> 44:58.195
Listen, I want you
to know something.

44:58.321 --> 44:59.404
You're welcome to stay
as long as you like.

44:59.530 --> 45:03.325
My mission is
to grow this family.

45:03.451 --> 45:05.952
Spread the word of God.

45:06.079 --> 45:10.791
Well, like I said,
we won't be staying for long.

45:11.918 --> 45:13.668
All right.

45:14.962 --> 45:17.547
He's a quiet one.

45:17.673 --> 45:19.758
Got many friends?

45:19.884 --> 45:21.843
I have no idea.

45:21.969 --> 45:23.428
A boy needs friends, you know.

45:23.554 --> 45:25.138
Jesus had 12 of them.

45:25.264 --> 45:26.681
Yeah.

45:26.682 --> 45:28.225
Well, look what good
that did him.

45:29.936 --> 45:31.686
Listen, we're having
a retreat tonight.

45:31.771 --> 45:32.938
Want to stick around?
The boy will love it.

45:33.064 --> 45:34.064
You gonna have
food there?

45:35.733 --> 45:38.693
We'll have food there.

45:38.778 --> 45:41.071
One piece of advice.

45:41.197 --> 45:43.031
What's that?

45:43.157 --> 45:46.701
You want to save a little room
for the coconut cream pie.

45:46.702 --> 45:48.453
Good to know.

45:49.705 --> 45:51.415
Louis, hello, my friend.

45:51.541 --> 45:52.958
- Hi.
- How are you, son?

45:53.084 --> 45:54.709
Good, thank you.

45:54.710 --> 45:55.710
I'm gonna sit here and
join you if you don't mind.

45:55.711 --> 45:56.962
It's fine.

45:57.088 --> 45:58.046
We're happy to have
you with us today.

45:58.172 --> 45:59.840
Happy to be here.

45:59.966 --> 46:02.509
So tell me about yourself.

46:39.130 --> 46:40.755
Hey.

46:40.756 --> 46:43.758
Louis. Louis?
Hey, hey, wake up.

46:47.763 --> 46:48.763
We gotta hit the road.
Come on.

46:48.764 --> 46:51.141
What the hell is...

46:55.688 --> 46:57.689
What the hell
are you doing?

46:57.773 --> 46:59.524
- Come on.
- I don't want... I'm not fucking leaving!

46:59.650 --> 47:01.485
Come on, it's time to go.

47:01.611 --> 47:04.362
- What the hell's your problem?
- Hey, come on!

47:06.073 --> 47:07.657
Come on!

47:14.790 --> 47:16.416
This is yours.

47:26.719 --> 47:28.386
I hate you.

47:29.472 --> 47:31.598
I think you were scared.

47:31.724 --> 47:34.976
You're scared they'd find out
you're a bad person.

47:35.102 --> 47:37.812
A wolf, like
the pastor said.

47:37.813 --> 47:40.774
A wolf?
He called me a wolf?

47:40.858 --> 47:43.818
Beware of false prophets
who wear sheep's clothing

47:43.903 --> 47:47.989
because really
they're ravenous wolves.

47:48.115 --> 47:51.159
He said that?

47:51.285 --> 47:55.080
That's...

47:55.206 --> 47:56.498
I'm not doing
this anymore.

47:56.624 --> 47:57.499
What do you mean,
you're not doing this?

47:57.625 --> 47:58.750
I'm not doing it.

47:58.834 --> 48:01.086
Hey, get up!
Come on!

48:01.212 --> 48:02.921
We've been over this!

48:03.047 --> 48:05.215
Hey, get up!

48:05.341 --> 48:06.841
We gotta keep moving.

48:09.303 --> 48:10.762
Hey!

48:10.846 --> 48:12.764
Can't just sit
around all day!

48:12.848 --> 48:14.849
Come on!
Let's go!

48:26.112 --> 48:28.321
Thank you.

48:28.447 --> 48:30.365
I need a lift for me
and my friend back here.

48:30.491 --> 48:32.617
Just take a minute.
Hold on one second.

48:32.743 --> 48:34.828
Louis! Come on!

48:43.963 --> 48:46.423
Louis.

49:05.901 --> 49:07.819
Grab our things and take
them to the room, will ya?

49:07.903 --> 49:08.987
I'm gonna go grab a drink.

49:09.113 --> 49:10.697
How long?

49:10.823 --> 49:13.033
I don't know.
As long as it takes me.

49:22.918 --> 49:25.503
Give me a whiskey
and a beer chaser.

49:58.162 --> 50:02.290
- Oh, God.
- Okay.

50:02.416 --> 50:03.958
Ah!

51:18.033 --> 51:19.633
I don't know where the damn kid is.

51:19.702 --> 51:20.618
How can you drink those things?

51:20.745 --> 51:22.036
They give me heartburn.

51:22.121 --> 51:26.166
Yeah? I think they're just
fine in the morning.

51:28.127 --> 51:30.211
Oh, there he is!

51:30.337 --> 51:31.796
Great.

51:31.922 --> 51:34.924
This is Louis,
Louis Moody.

51:35.050 --> 51:37.051
- Hi.
- Hi, honey.

51:37.052 --> 51:41.389
I'm Mary.
This is Rose.

51:41.515 --> 51:43.308
Mary and Rose are
headed into Mexico.

51:43.434 --> 51:45.393
That's right.
You're gonna pay for the gas, huh?

51:45.519 --> 51:47.061
'Cause she pissed off
our meal ticket!

51:47.062 --> 51:49.063
Oh, Rose, shut up!

51:49.064 --> 51:51.065
So there you have it.

51:51.150 --> 51:52.550
Well, get in.
You're driving, right?

51:52.651 --> 51:53.902
Oh, yeah.

51:58.073 --> 51:59.866
Should I put
the stuff in the trunk?

51:59.992 --> 52:01.451
- Just throw it in the back.
- Back there?

52:01.577 --> 52:04.454
Why don't you guys both
get in the way back?

52:04.580 --> 52:08.500
We got some adult
conversations to have.

52:12.755 --> 52:13.880
Get in.

52:14.006 --> 52:15.465
This is gonna be fun.

52:29.104 --> 52:32.106
Were you the one
knocking on my wall?

52:32.191 --> 52:34.651
No.

52:34.777 --> 52:37.779
Yes, you were.

52:37.905 --> 52:39.155
Why didn't
you knock back?

52:39.281 --> 52:40.698
That's how it works,
you know.

52:40.825 --> 52:41.991
You're supposed
to knock back.

52:42.117 --> 52:44.244
I don't know.

52:44.370 --> 52:46.079
How old are you anyway?

52:46.163 --> 52:48.456
I'm 13.

52:48.582 --> 52:51.167
Well, I mean, I guess, 14.

52:51.293 --> 52:54.462
I'm 13.

52:54.588 --> 52:56.881
Is that your mom?

52:57.007 --> 52:58.883
You could call her that.

52:59.009 --> 53:03.429
It's that you don't look
like each other, so...

53:03.556 --> 53:04.848
I was just wondering.

53:04.974 --> 53:08.226
People say I take
after my dad.

53:08.352 --> 53:10.144
People say I take
after my mom.

53:19.530 --> 53:22.907
That's an amethyst.

53:23.033 --> 53:24.617
That's turquoise.

53:24.743 --> 53:27.912
Oh, I know turquoise. I got a...
check that out.

53:28.038 --> 53:29.330
Brand new ring.

53:29.456 --> 53:32.083
- That's nice.
- Turquoise.

53:32.167 --> 53:34.168
Well, that's what
they call kismet.

53:34.169 --> 53:36.087
Oh, yeah?
What's that mean?

53:36.171 --> 53:39.674
Well, it's a Middle Eastern word
for coincidence or serendipity.

53:39.800 --> 53:42.552
Ah, kismet.

53:42.678 --> 53:43.970
Kismet.

53:44.096 --> 53:46.764
So here's the deal.
You pay for the gas.

53:46.891 --> 53:48.291
We'll pay for our
own lodging, okay?

53:48.350 --> 53:49.976
All right.

53:50.102 --> 53:52.979
You know, I don't just let
any stranger into my car.

53:53.105 --> 53:55.189
These are unique circumstances,
you understand?

53:55.274 --> 53:57.942
I understand
completely,

53:58.068 --> 54:00.862
and we're not exactly
strangers at this point.

54:00.988 --> 54:03.740
Just don't get any ideas,
lover boy.

54:03.866 --> 54:05.199
I won't get any.

54:05.200 --> 54:08.119
Well, I might get
a couple ideas.

54:08.203 --> 54:10.622
I'll just keep 'em
right up in here.

54:37.274 --> 54:39.317
Don't go telling 'em
too much about yourself.

54:39.443 --> 54:42.695
Remember what
I told you about women.

54:42.821 --> 54:45.782
Well, look at us.
Just like one big happy family.

54:45.908 --> 54:47.867
Hardly.

54:47.952 --> 54:48.868
Hey, you know what I think we
should do?

54:48.953 --> 54:50.453
We should go shopping.

54:50.537 --> 54:53.206
Might as well have a little fun
while we're on this trip, right?

54:53.290 --> 54:55.917
I don't know.

54:56.043 --> 54:57.293
She loves buying stuff.

54:59.880 --> 55:04.133
All right, y'all.
What do you think?

55:04.259 --> 55:07.011
Well, well, well.
Just like Miss America.

55:08.138 --> 55:09.973
Can we go now?

55:10.099 --> 55:11.432
I'm gonna buy that for you.

55:11.558 --> 55:14.435
- We need that money.
- I got plenty.

55:14.561 --> 55:17.271
I'm gonna go pick out
some things for the kids.

55:25.698 --> 55:27.323
Oh, yeah.

55:30.953 --> 55:32.286
I hate dresses.

55:32.287 --> 55:33.871
You two look adorable.

55:33.998 --> 55:36.499
You look nice.

55:53.767 --> 55:56.060
You know, I'm usually a pretty
good judge of character.

55:56.186 --> 55:59.397
But I'm gonna admit
I read y'all wrong.

55:59.523 --> 56:03.109
I thought you were gonna
be greedy and selfish

56:03.235 --> 56:05.570
like most of the men
I've been with.

56:05.696 --> 56:10.324
But you ain't
and I like you.

56:10.325 --> 56:13.327
Yeah? Well,
I like you too.

56:16.123 --> 56:18.249
You know, my mama
always said,

56:18.333 --> 56:23.254
"Don't waste time waiting
for the perfect man because,

56:23.338 --> 56:27.008
well, life is too
goddamned short."

56:27.134 --> 56:29.343
That's what she said?

56:43.358 --> 56:45.902
Wish I could just
run away, don't you?

56:48.363 --> 56:50.281
I don't know.

56:50.365 --> 56:53.951
There's nowhere
to really run off to.

56:55.621 --> 56:57.955
Where would you even go?

56:58.082 --> 57:01.542
Ever been to the beach?

57:01.668 --> 57:04.462
Never really had a chance to.

57:04.588 --> 57:06.380
That's where I'd go.

57:06.381 --> 57:08.299
Somewhere with a beach.

57:08.383 --> 57:11.302
You could always come
to the beach with me and,

57:11.386 --> 57:14.305
you know, we could have
our sandcastle house.

57:14.389 --> 57:18.142
Go fishing.
We'd survive on fish.

57:18.268 --> 57:21.562
Could be a lot worse.

57:21.688 --> 57:24.315
If you could, if there
was any place on Earth

57:24.399 --> 57:26.901
you could run away to,
where'd you run?

57:27.027 --> 57:30.196
If I had to choose?

57:32.908 --> 57:34.617
I'd probably go home.

57:36.078 --> 57:38.412
Pretty exciting, right?

57:38.413 --> 57:40.832
Is that in New Mexico?

57:43.627 --> 57:45.461
I don't know.

58:24.459 --> 58:27.461
Well, come on.

58:27.462 --> 58:29.922
Tell me something
about yourself.

58:30.048 --> 58:31.549
Well, there's not
much to tell.

58:31.675 --> 58:33.509
I don't much like
talking about myself.

58:33.635 --> 58:35.261
It's not easy for me.

58:35.387 --> 58:38.848
Fine.
What about the boy?

58:38.974 --> 58:40.808
His mother died.

58:44.980 --> 58:46.480
And?

58:46.481 --> 58:48.816
I'm taking him to live
with his grandparents.

58:48.942 --> 58:52.236
Well, why go through
all that trouble?

58:52.362 --> 58:54.655
Well, because
he's a good kid.

58:54.781 --> 58:56.616
I don't mind
spending time with him.

58:56.742 --> 58:58.784
Uh-huh.

58:58.911 --> 59:00.536
What's in it for you?

59:03.290 --> 59:06.375
There ain't nothing
in it for me.

59:06.501 --> 59:10.004
You're lying.

59:10.130 --> 59:11.672
You're a liar.

59:14.301 --> 59:16.385
Is he yours?

59:25.312 --> 59:27.063
Look at you.

59:45.332 --> 59:47.875
I ain't no fucking liar.

01:00:00.055 --> 01:00:02.556
You're way better.
I'm not even making...

01:00:02.557 --> 01:00:04.058
Snap, snap, clap.

01:00:04.184 --> 01:00:05.768
I can't snap.

01:00:09.815 --> 01:00:13.526
Hey, you know we're not far
from my grandparents' house.

01:00:13.610 --> 01:00:14.690
My mom said it snows there.

01:00:14.778 --> 01:00:16.570
I've never seen snow.

01:00:16.571 --> 01:00:18.739
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:00:18.865 --> 01:00:21.575
You should come.

01:00:21.576 --> 01:00:24.245
I mean, you know,
if you wanted.

01:00:24.371 --> 01:00:25.579
It'd be cool.

01:00:25.580 --> 01:00:29.041
Yeah. Sounds fun.

01:00:29.167 --> 01:00:30.584
Yeah.

01:00:42.597 --> 01:00:44.181
Yeah?

01:00:44.308 --> 01:00:46.600
Hey, let me talk to George.
It's John.

01:00:46.685 --> 01:00:48.602
John?

01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:49.895
How's the head?

01:00:50.022 --> 01:00:52.189
Oh, just fine.
How's your sister?

01:00:58.488 --> 01:01:01.365
Hey, John.
Any luck in finding my money?

01:01:01.491 --> 01:01:03.200
I've got the rest
of your $10,000.

01:01:03.327 --> 01:01:05.202
So you're 10 short.

01:01:05.329 --> 01:01:07.496
How about this?
I bring you what I have.

01:01:07.622 --> 01:01:09.165
Or you can come
looking for the rest.

01:01:09.291 --> 01:01:13.627
Maybe I'll go and look
for it in New Mexico.

01:01:13.628 --> 01:01:16.172
Farmington, New Mexico.

01:01:16.298 --> 01:01:18.924
Maybe I'll find
my money over there.

01:01:19.051 --> 01:01:21.344
I don't know what
you're talking about.

01:01:21.470 --> 01:01:23.512
Of course you don't.

01:01:23.638 --> 01:01:26.015
$20,000, John.

01:01:26.141 --> 01:01:28.851
See you soon.

01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:54.001
Our hometown ain't
far from here.

01:01:54.127 --> 01:01:55.961
Y'all can stay with us
if you want.

01:01:56.088 --> 01:01:58.005
Oh, yeah? How long?

01:01:59.674 --> 01:02:01.467
As long as you want.

01:02:03.553 --> 01:02:05.179
Yeah, I don't know about that.

01:02:05.305 --> 01:02:08.682
I think that this little thing

01:02:08.683 --> 01:02:10.434
has probably run its course.

01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:13.437
So we should
probably get going.

01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:15.898
Wow.

01:02:18.777 --> 01:02:20.694
Well, fuck you, John.

01:02:20.779 --> 01:02:24.657
Well, I think we've already
done that, haven't we?

01:02:29.204 --> 01:02:30.788
Louis.

01:02:30.914 --> 01:02:33.374
John tell you why
he's taking you home?

01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:35.060
Yeah, he's taking me
to my grandparents.

01:02:35.168 --> 01:02:37.086
No, baby.
Did he tell you why?

01:02:37.212 --> 01:02:39.004
I think you should probably
quit while you're ahead.

01:02:39.131 --> 01:02:43.634
Well, I think I'd like
to fill in the blanks, okay?

01:02:43.718 --> 01:02:46.429
John strikes me as
the type of guy who's failed

01:02:46.555 --> 01:02:47.847
at just about everything
he's ever done.

01:02:47.973 --> 01:02:49.473
Am I right?

01:02:49.599 --> 01:02:52.852
You always had luck with
the ladies, didn't you?

01:02:52.978 --> 01:02:55.479
But that never lasted

01:02:55.605 --> 01:02:57.731
and somewhere along the way,
all those big plans,

01:02:57.816 --> 01:03:01.402
well, they fell apart
and you got desperate.

01:03:01.528 --> 01:03:03.863
A little lonely.

01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:05.781
That's why the idea
of dragging him around,

01:03:05.907 --> 01:03:08.451
well, wasn't so bad,
was it?

01:03:08.577 --> 01:03:09.869
Mom...

01:03:09.995 --> 01:03:13.873
Don't worry, honey.
He ain't like us.

01:03:13.999 --> 01:03:17.918
Men like him don't have the balls
to survive in the real world.

01:03:18.044 --> 01:03:19.503
All right, listen, lady...

01:03:19.629 --> 01:03:23.048
But the one who's got
the most to lose is you.

01:03:23.175 --> 01:03:25.759
Do you even know
who he is, honey?

01:03:25.760 --> 01:03:27.803
'Cause he's using you.

01:03:29.931 --> 01:03:32.766
Just like he used me.

01:03:37.481 --> 01:03:39.690
Just like he
uses everybody.

01:03:39.774 --> 01:03:41.984
This is bullshit.

01:03:48.783 --> 01:03:51.118
They always run.

01:04:09.679 --> 01:04:10.930
John?

01:04:11.056 --> 01:04:12.598
- John?
- Get back inside, Louis!

01:04:12.724 --> 01:04:15.809
John, let's just leave.
We can find another ride.

01:04:15.810 --> 01:04:18.854
Louis, get back inside.

01:04:23.235 --> 01:04:25.694
John, she doesn't
know anything about you.

01:04:25.820 --> 01:04:28.072
She's right, Louis.
I am afraid.

01:04:28.198 --> 01:04:32.826
And I just can't take living
like everyone else, you know?

01:04:32.911 --> 01:04:36.121
The problem is, there's
certain things about me

01:04:36.248 --> 01:04:37.998
that I just can't
seem to change.

01:04:38.124 --> 01:04:41.627
John.
John, stop.

01:04:41.753 --> 01:04:43.379
John!

01:04:59.145 --> 01:05:00.813
I knew there was
something wrong with him.

01:05:00.897 --> 01:05:03.190
Come on, Louis.
We're gonna take you home.

01:05:03.316 --> 01:05:05.859
It's not gonna
end well, honey.

01:05:08.238 --> 01:05:09.863
Come on, get in.

01:05:09.864 --> 01:05:11.532
Come on, it's okay.

01:05:21.793 --> 01:05:24.878
Louis! What are you doing?

01:05:29.134 --> 01:05:32.386
Get over!

01:05:32.512 --> 01:05:33.887
Get down!

01:05:40.895 --> 01:05:43.022
God damn it!

01:05:44.816 --> 01:05:46.442
God damn it!

01:05:46.568 --> 01:05:49.194
This is a lot of money.

01:05:49.321 --> 01:05:51.947
We could fly to Farmington
if we wanted.

01:06:05.420 --> 01:06:08.213
You know what she said
about you wasn't true.

01:06:08.340 --> 01:06:12.843
I don't know, she split me
wide open, didn't she?

01:06:12.927 --> 01:06:15.846
You know, when I was in jail,

01:06:15.930 --> 01:06:17.306
everyone wanted
to blame everyone else

01:06:17.432 --> 01:06:19.850
for who they
turned out to be.

01:06:19.934 --> 01:06:23.562
Mom, dad, girlfriend, wife.

01:06:25.940 --> 01:06:28.942
I made a lot
of mistakes in my life.

01:06:31.446 --> 01:06:34.406
But they were my mistakes,
nobody else's.

01:06:35.867 --> 01:06:38.202
They're mine.

01:06:38.328 --> 01:06:39.870
You know, when you
get older, Louis,

01:06:39.954 --> 01:06:44.500
all those mistakes start
piling up inside you.

01:06:44.626 --> 01:06:47.002
Just a pile of mistakes.

01:06:49.005 --> 01:06:51.548
Regrets, blame.

01:06:54.969 --> 01:06:57.846
It's enough to make you
feel sick to your stomach.

01:07:00.225 --> 01:07:02.976
Secrets make me
feel like that.

01:07:02.977 --> 01:07:05.813
Yeah, secrets, too.

01:07:09.818 --> 01:07:11.235
You got many secrets?

01:07:11.361 --> 01:07:14.321
Yeah, plenty.

01:07:14.447 --> 01:07:15.989
How about you?

01:07:18.785 --> 01:07:20.869
Yeah.

01:07:20.995 --> 01:07:22.538
I like that girl.

01:07:22.664 --> 01:07:23.997
Shit, that ain't no secret.

01:07:27.001 --> 01:07:29.420
Yeah.

01:07:33.883 --> 01:07:36.009
Tell me one
of your secrets.

01:07:40.807 --> 01:07:43.016
Maybe some other time.

01:08:33.067 --> 01:08:35.027
John?

01:08:45.705 --> 01:08:47.413
John?

01:08:52.754 --> 01:08:54.421
John?

01:09:08.185 --> 01:09:09.560
Hey!

01:09:14.274 --> 01:09:15.859
Look at that.

01:09:38.758 --> 01:09:41.134
Hey, we need some
food for the road.

01:09:41.219 --> 01:09:44.429
All right.
I'm gonna go grab some gas.

01:09:44.555 --> 01:09:46.055
Let's meet back
here in ten minutes.

01:09:46.140 --> 01:09:48.140
All right,
you go first.

01:09:54.607 --> 01:09:56.149
Watch out.

01:10:01.406 --> 01:10:03.198
Go on!

01:10:09.831 --> 01:10:12.833
Our APO here is 96309.

01:10:12.959 --> 01:10:15.419
So drop us a line,
anytime, APO 96309

01:10:15.545 --> 01:10:16.420
and we'll get it on.

01:10:16.546 --> 01:10:17.671
Anything else?

01:10:17.797 --> 01:10:19.548
Oh, that's it.
Thanks.

